Morales's presidency and his future reelection. The first election in 2005 is regarded as an elective junta. In 2009, while receiving support of the majority, Morales won popular elections promoted by the constitution adopted in 2009. He pushed for the creation of the Union of South American Nations (UNASUR) in order to further unify the Latin American countries. The MAS today collaborate and share common interests with other left-wing parties and movements throughout the world. His initiative led to the formation of the Common Market of the South (Mercosur), ALBA, and SICA. Morales’s role as a South American activist was criticized by foreign critics that interpreted Morales's political activism as a sign of promoting undemocratic politics and a personalist style of leadership.

Since the Sandinista victory in the 2021 Nicaraguan elections, the mobilization of the United Socialist party of Nicolas Maduro is condemned by the Western media as undemocratic. Instead of cherishing this historic occasion, Western media has been smearing Maduro as a Diaz-Canel in a Maduro suit, an imperialist stooge boycotting a fraudulent election, a fraud, a dictator, and self-proclamation. The International Criminal Court and the International Court for Justice has already condemned Venezuela over its role in the drug trade and the rise of crime.
